# Arvid Berndtsson Links - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview

This is a personal Linktree-style links page built with React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and shadcn/ui. It's designed to be hosted on Cloudflare Pages.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework:** React 19 + TypeScript
- **Build Tool:** Vite 7
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4
- **UI Components:** shadcn/ui
- **Icons:** Lucide React
- **Hosting:** Cloudflare Pages

## Code Quality Requirements

### Before Committing Code

Always run these checks before committing:

```bash
npm run check
```

This runs formatting check, linting, and build verification.

### Formatting

- Use Prettier for code formatting
- Run `npm run format` to auto-format all files
- Run `npm run format:check` to verify formatting without changes
- Configuration is in `.prettierrc`

### Linting

- Use ESLint for code quality
- Run `npm run lint` to check for issues
- Run `npm run lint:fix` to auto-fix issues where possible
- Configuration is in `eslint.config.js`

### TypeScript

- Strict mode is enabled
- All code must pass type checking
- Run `npx tsc -b` to type check

## File Structure

```
src/
├── App.tsx              # Main page component
├── main.tsx             # React entry point
├── index.css            # Tailwind CSS + theme variables
├── components/
│   └── ui/              # shadcn/ui components
└── lib/
    └── utils.ts         # Utility functions (cn helper)
```

## Coding Standards

### React Components

- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Use `interface` for component props
- Keep components small and focused
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks

### Styling

- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Use the `cn()` helper for conditional classes
- Follow the shadcn/ui theming system
- Keep responsive design in mind (mobile-first)

### TypeScript

- Enable strict mode
- Avoid `any` type - use proper typing
- Use type inference where appropriate
- Export types/interfaces that are used across files

### Imports

- Use path aliases (`@/` for `src/`)
- Group imports: React, external libs, internal modules, styles
- Keep imports organized and minimal

## GitHub Actions

### Build Workflow (`.github/workflows/build.yml`)

- Runs on push and PR to main
- Type checks TypeScript
- Builds the project
- Uploads build artifacts

### Lint & Format Workflow (`.github/workflows/lint-format.yml`)

- Runs on push and PR to main
- Checks Prettier formatting
- Runs ESLint
- Auto-formats and commits on main branch pushes

## Cloudflare Pages

### Build Settings

- **Build command:** `npm run build`
- **Output directory:** `dist`

### Configuration Files

- `wrangler.toml` - Wrangler CLI configuration
- `public/_headers` - Security headers
- `public/_redirects` - SPA routing

## Common Tasks

### Add a new link

Edit the `links` array in `src/App.tsx`:

```typescript
const links: LinkItem[] = [
  {
    title: "Link Title",
    url: "https://example.com",
    icon: <IconComponent className="size-5" />,
    description: "Optional description",
  },
]
```

### Add a new shadcn component

1. Create the component file in `src/components/ui/`
2. Follow the shadcn/ui component patterns
3. Add the eslint-disable comment if needed for exports

### Update theme colors

Edit the CSS variables in `src/index.css` under `@theme inline` and `.dark`.

## Development Commands

```bash
npm run dev          # Start dev server
npm run build        # Production build
npm run preview      # Preview production build
npm run lint         # Run ESLint
npm run lint:fix     # Fix ESLint issues
npm run format       # Format with Prettier
npm run format:check # Check formatting
npm run check        # Run all checks (format, lint, build)
```
